🎯 Aim
To build a Power Query pipeline that combines multiple monthly files from a folder, standardizes the data, unpivots wide tables, removes duplicates, assigns correct data types, and prepares a data quality summary.
🧭 Algorithm (12 Points)
1.	Open Excel / Power BI and choose Get Data → From Folder.
2.	Select the folder containing Jan_Sales and Feb_Sales files.
3.	Click Combine & Transform to merge the monthly files.
4.	Rename column headers to standard names (order_id, order_date, city).
5.	Use Trim and Clean to standardize city text values.
6.	Convert columns to proper data types (date, text, whole number).
7.	Select Product_A, Product_B, Product_C columns.
8.	Apply Unpivot Columns to convert wide table into long format.
9.	Rename columns as product and quantity.
10.	Remove duplicate records using order_id.
11.	Duplicate the query and apply Group By → Count Rows for quality check.
12.	Prepare a Data Quality Summary and load the final cleaned table.

